The paper proposes a new algorithm for distributional reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on the parameterization of estimated distributions, which is a common topic in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm uses neural networks, which are a common tool in deep learning (cs.DL). The experiments are conducted on Atari games, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
